'''Morality''' (from Latin ''{{lang|la|moralitas}}'' "manner, character, proper behaviour") refers to the concept of human action which pertains to matters of right and wrong—also referred to as "[[good and evil]]"—used within three contexts: individual [[distinction]]; systems of valued [[principle]]s—sometimes called [[Code of conduct|conduct morality]]—shared within a [[cultural]], [[religion|religious]], [[secular]] or [[philosophical]] community.
